    {
      "id": 360418,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>One of the following molecules <b>(a)</b>–<b>(d)</b> is D-erythrose 4-phosphate, an intermediate in the Calvin photosynthetic cycle by which plants incorporate CO<sub>2</sub> into carbohydrates. If D-erythrose 4-phosphate has <i>R</i> stereochemistry at both chirality centers, which of the structures is it? Which of the remaining three structures is the enantiomer of D-erythrose 4-phosphate, and which are diastereomers?</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdVlYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--82a6487165bedf0c8572dcde5544eb56054aa908/OChem_05_06_003a.jpg\" alt=\"Vertically, aldehyde dashed bond carbon bond carbon dashed bond C H 2 phosphate. C 2 and C 3 both have hydrogen (wedge, left) and hydroxyl (wedge, right).\">\n <b>(b)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdWNYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6bc0b12e27b697144d2f811a27808d54900f62d4/OChem_05_06_003b.jpg\" alt=\"Vertically, aldehyde dashed bond carbon bond carbon dashed bond C H 2 phosphate. C 2 has hydroxyl (left), H on wedges, C 3 has hydrogen (left), hydroxyl on wedges.\">\n <b>(c)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdWdYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--22b3fba309232b882e853f53b449773c33a92b18/OChem_05_06_003c.jpg\" alt=\"Vertically, aldehyde dashed bond carbon bond carbon dashed bond C H 2 phosphate. C 2 has hydrogen (left), hydroxyl on wedges, C 3 has hydroxyl (left), hydrogen on wedges.\">\n <b>(d)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdWtYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--7bf667a1b92067951d9b93276028b01c11c20884/OChem_05_06_003d.jpg\" alt=\"Vertically, aldehyde dashed bond carbon bond carbon dashed bond C H 2 phosphate. C 2 and C 3 both have hydroxyl (wedge, left) and hydrogen (wedge, right).\"></p>",
      "answers": [],
